<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.5.4</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.5.4</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.5.4</Version>
    <!-- v0.6.5.3a — InformationalVersion is the .NET-canonical home for human-friendly
         version strings that can include letter suffixes ("0.6.5.3a"), pre-release
         markers ("-rc1"), build metadata, etc. The numeric AssemblyVersion above is
         still strictly Major.Minor.Build.Revision (validated by CS7034); we tick it
         forward by one whenever the binary changes, regardless of how the display
         version looks. ResolveVersion() in UI/MainWindow.cs prefers this string for
         everything user-visible (header pill, About tab, /ttinfo output). -->
    <InformationalVersion>0.6.5.3a</InformationalVersion>
    <IncludeSourceRevisionInInformationalVersion>false</IncludeSourceRevisionInInformationalVersion>
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics — BiS planner, gear inventory reader, materia advisor for FFXIV. v0.6.5.3a is a small patch on top of v0.6.5.3 that targets BUG-001 (the character-panel Materia Advisor header ghost-text artifact that v0.6.5.2 and v0.6.5.3 both attempted to fix and missed). The "a" suffix signals this is a focused contained patch — not a regular x-bump — sitting between v0.6.5.3 and the planned v0.6.5.4 ("Mobile Site"). The intervention this time: hypothesis H1 from the CharacterPanelRefined deep dive — removing the two-line bidirectional sibling-link patch in StatusPanelInjector.cs AddStatRow that CPR's upstream pattern does not have. The patch was added defensively in earlier development to keep the cloned node's NextSiblingNode chain consistent with its PrevSiblingNode chain; on review against CPR, it's likely causing UldManager.UpdateDrawNodeList to enumerate cloned label nodes via two traversal paths, resulting in double-rendering at slightly offset draw priorities. The visible ghost-text signature matches that hypothesis. Status: pending in-game verification. Core and Web at v0.6.5.3 awaiting lockstep bump until this candidate is confirmed working. AssemblyVersion ticks numerically to 0.6.5.4 (the .NET version system can't represent letter suffixes in AssemblyVersion); the human-facing version string "0.6.5.3a" lives in InformationalVersion. See BUG_HUNT_AND_ROADMAP.md for the experiment plan and CPR_DEEP_DIVE.md for the analysis.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!--
    v0.6.3: ProjectReference to the shared GearGoblin.Core library.
    Path assumes the standard sibling-of-grandparent layout:

        D:\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\        (Core, this reference's target)
        D:\GearGoblin-v0.1\GearGoblin\                  (this project)
        D:\TonberryTactics-workspace\TonberryTactics\   (web, mirrors this same reference)

    If Core lives somewhere else on your machine, update the path to
    point at your local clone. The web's csproj uses the same relative
    pattern so both halves resolve to the same library on disk.

    Plugin's existing MeldOptimizer (already job-aware via JobProfile)
    continues to function unchanged in v0.6.3 — Core integration on
    the plugin side is incremental, tracked for v0.7.x alongside the
    CPR-replacement work. Today's ProjectReference exists so future
    migrations are mechanical rather than gated on adding a dependency.
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\..\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\GearGoblin.Core.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
